<body>

<header>
    <h1>Basic Malware Analysis</h1>
    <p>
        A beginner-friendly introduction to malware analysis concepts,
        techniques, and tools used by reverse engineers and detection engineers.
    </p>
</header>

<main>

<section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
        Malware analysis is the process of dissecting malicious software to
        understand its behavior, functionality, and intent.
        The insights gained help in detection, prevention, and incident response.
    </p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Analysis Types</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Static Analysis</strong> – Inspecting malware without executing it</li>
        <li><strong>Dynamic Analysis</strong> – Observing runtime behavior in a sandbox</li>
        <li><strong>Code Analysis</strong> – Reverse engineering assembly or decompiled code</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Basic Static Analysis</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>File hashes (MD5, SHA256)</li>
        <li>Strings analysis</li>
        <li>PE headers and imports</li>
        <li>Packer and compiler detection</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="box">
        Tools commonly used:
        <ul>
            <li><code>strings</code></li>
            <li><code>Detect It Easy</code></li>
            <li><code>PE-bear</code></li>
            <li><code>Ghidra</code></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Basic Dynamic Analysis</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Process and thread creation</li>
        <li>File system modifications</li>
        <li>Registry persistence</li>
        <li>Network traffic analysis</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="box">
        Tools commonly used:
        <ul>
            <li><code>Process Monitor</code></li>
            <li><code>Process Explorer</code></li>
            <li><code>FakeNet-NG</code></li>
            <li><code>Wireshark</code></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Common Malware Techniques</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Persistence via registry or scheduled tasks</li>
        <li>Command and Control (C2)</li>
        <li>Code injection</li>
        <li>Credential harvesting</li>
        <li>Anti-debugging and anti-VM checks</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Safe Analysis Practices</h2>
    <div class="box">
        <ul>
            <li>Use isolated virtual machines</li>
            <li>Disable shared folders and clipboard</li>
            <li>Snapshot before execution</li>
            <li>Never analyze malware on the host OS</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

</main>

